        "advice": [
            {
                "text": "Kindly correlate clinically."
            },
            {
                "text": "Individuals at increased risk of pregnancy-associated and oral contraceptive related complications should be evaluated."
            },
            {
                "text": "Individuals that are positive for the Factor V Leiden mutation can be advised of the risk of thrombotic events for other family members."
            },
            {
                "text": "Heterozygotes have an increased risk of thrombosis of 5 to 10 fold, without other concomitant risk factors."
            }
        ],
        "interpretation": "ANTITHROMBIN ACTIVITY, PLASMA - Antithrombin (AT) is synthesized in the liver and in addition to inhibiting thrombin, it inactivated activated factors IX, X, XI, XII and tissue factor bound VIIa. Its deficiency is one of the several causes of venous thromboembolism. AT deficiency may be congenital or acquired. functional levels are low but antigenic levels are normal. Acquired deficiency of AT is seen in DIC, liver disease, nephrotic syndrome, pre-ecclampsia, women on oral contraceptive and pregnancy. Thrombin inhibitors may lead to overestimation of AT. In men the AT levels decrease with age. In children the levels are low until the age of 6 months, when it reaches adult levels. CARDIOLIPIN ANTIBODIES PROFILE(IGG,IGM), SERUM-Antibodies against Cardiolipin belong to the group of anti-phospholipid antibodies specific for negatively charged phospholipids, components of biological membranes. These antibodies are important as a diagnostic marker for a disorder called the 'anti phospholipid syndrome' (APS). Homocysteine, is a thiol containing amino acid and intermediary in the sulfur-amino acid metabolism pathways, it serves as a link between methionine cycle to folate cycle. ... Other factors that may influence and increase plasma homocysteine include: Age, Smoking, poor diet/cofactor deficiencies, and Hypothyroidism. Note : This test is standardized and validated at Agilus Diagnostics."
    },
